        "timestamp": "2017-09-07 02:42:50.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nIt seems dependencies that appear in oparent and we inherit keep messing with our loads at different points, see the checkstyle dependency that gets into our executables:\n\nArchive:  install-drools.zip\n  inflating: policy-management.conf  \n  inflating: feature-healthcheck.conf  \n  inflating: base.conf               \n  inflating: base-1.1.0-SNAPSHOT.tar.gz  \n  inflating: policy-management-1.1.0-SNAPSHOT.zip  \n  inflating: feature-healthcheck-1.1.0-SNAPSHOT.zip  \n  inflating: feature-eelf-1.1.0-SNAPSHOT.zip  \n  inflating: feature-session-persistence-1.1.0-SNAPSHOT.zip  \n  inflating: checkstyle-1.0.0-20170906.151316-29.jar  \nArchive:  apps.zip\n  inflating: README.apps.txt         \n  inflating: basex-1.1.0-SNAPSHOT.tar.gz  \n  inflating: artifacts-1.1.0-SNAPSHOT.zip  \n\u001b[91mreplace checkstyle-1.0.0-20170906.151316-29.jar? [y]es, [n]o, [A]ll, [N]one, [r]ename:  NULL\n(EOF or read error, treating as \"[N]one\" ...)\n\u001b[0mThe command '/bin/sh -c unzip install-drools.zip &&     unzip apps.zip &&     rm install-drools.zip apps.zip &&     chown -R policy * &&     chmod +x *.sh' returned a non-zero code: 1\nDocker build failed",
